#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""chain_033 Ashby submit runner — connect to OpenClaw browser on port 18800
and execute a compiled plan end-to-end via Playwright CDP.

Usage:
  python3 chain033_ashby_runner.py <plan_path> [--no-submit] [--no-captcha]

Pipeline per role:
  1. Connect over CDP, open a fresh page (so we don't clobber other tabs).
  2. Navigate to apply URL.
  3. For each plan step, dispatch:
     - browser.open      -> page.goto
     - sleep             -> page.wait_for_timeout
     - browser.act.evaluate (inlined fn) -> page.evaluate
     - ashby.type_text_fields -> dispatch via CDP keystrokes per text field
     - ashby.upload_resume_via_visible_button -> use input[type=file] direct
     - ashby.maybe_solve_recaptcha_v3 -> CapSolver + inject token
  4. Read submit-button click result. Wait for "Application submitted" /
     redirect. Return SUCCESS/FAILED.
"""
